CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F328A1784733508
OL,3,CTwo riders die in separate British
OL,4,CEventing competitions
OL,6,FRosie Williams, Chief Executive of
OL,7,FBritish Eventing, said: "The British
OL,8,FEventing community is heartbroken. On
OL,9,Fbehalf of everyone at British
OL,10,FEventing, I want to extend our deepest
OL,11,Fcondolences to Kerry and Sophie's
OL,12,Ffamilies, friends and loved ones at
OL,13,Fthis devastating time. Our thoughts
OL,14,Fare also with their fellow
OL,15,Fcompetitors, organisers, officials,
OL,16,Fvolunteers and everyone who has been
OL,17,Faffected by these tragic events.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G4/7
OL,2,W/.!+.!/*%/.!+,*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BBorder NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,329,320,120,260,000,100
PN,32805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F328A1784733508
OL,3,CTwo riders die in separate British
OL,4,CEventing competitions
OL,6,F"We are immensely grateful to the
OL,7,Forganisers, doctors, paramedics,
OL,8,Fveterinary teams, officials and
OL,9,Femergency services at both events for
OL,10,Fthe professionalism, compassion and
OL,11,Fcare they showed in the most difficult
OL,12,Fof circumstances."
OL,14,FShe added: "The loss of two members of
OL,15,Four eventing family on the same day is
OL,16,Falmost beyond words, and we know the
OL,17,Fsadness of these events will be felt
OL,18,Fprofoundly across the sport for some
OL,19,Ftime to come."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G5/7
